    <h1>Crew Calendar Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Effective date:</strong> To be updated before public release.</p>

    <p>Crew Calendar is operated by Twenty Over All LLC. This policy explains how Crew Calendar handles information when you use the app.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>Crew Calendar may collect account information such as an email address if you choose email sign-in. The app also stores user-created calendar content such as crew names, invite codes, members, birthdays, availability blocks, vacations, and shared planning items.</p>

    <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>We use this information to provide shared calendar, crew invite, availability, and sync features.</p>

    <h2>Cloud Services</h2>
    <p>Crew Calendar uses Firebase services, including Firebase Authentication and Cloud Firestore, to authenticate users and sync shared calendar data across devices.</p>

    <h2>Sharing</h2>
    <p>Your crew calendar information is shared with members who join your crew using an invite code. We do not sell personal information.</p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>Data is transmitted using encrypted connections. No method of storage or transmission is perfect, but we use standard cloud security practices through Firebase.</p>

    <h2>Data Deletion</h2>
    <p>Before public release, Crew Calendar will include a clearer data deletion process. For beta testing, contact us to request deletion of test data.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions? Contact: ibunique.lw@gmail.com</p>
  </main>
